hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Relevant relations:  
$$\sigma_m\approx\frac{2.5}{\ln10}\frac1{\rm SNR},\quad 
\mathrm{SNR}=\frac{N_\star}{\sqrt{N_\star+N_{\rm sky}}},\quad 
N_\star=R_S\,t,\;N_{\rm sky}=R_{\rm sky}\,t.$$  
The total $B\!-\!V$ error is  
$$\sigma_{B-V}^2=\sigma_{m_B}^2+\sigma_{m_V}^2
=\Bigl(\frac{2.5}{\ln10}\Bigr)^2\Bigl(\frac1{\mathrm{SNR}_B^2}+\frac1{\mathrm{SNR}_V^2}\Bigr).$$  
2. Express each SNR:  
$$\mathrm{SNR}_B=\frac{R_{S,B}\,t_B}{\sqrt{(R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B})\,t_B}}
=\frac{R_{S,B}\sqrt{t_B}}{\sqrt{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}},
\quad\frac1{\mathrm{SNR}_B^2}
=\frac{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}{R_{S,B}^2\,t_B},$$  
and similarly for the V‚Äêfilter with $t_V$.  Hence  
$$\sigma_{B-V}^2
=\Bigl(\frac{2.5}{\ln10}\Bigr)^2\Bigl(\frac{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}{R_{S,B}^2\,t_B}
+\frac{R_{S,V}+R_{sky,V}}{R_{S,V}^2\,t_V}\Bigr).$$  
3. Minimize under $t_B+t_V=T_{tot}$ by Lagrange multipliers:  
$$\frac{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}{R_{S,B}^2\,t_B^2}
=\frac{R_{S,V}+R_{sky,V}}{R_{S,V}^2\,t_V^2}
\;\Rightarrow\;\frac{t_B}{t_V}
=\sqrt{\frac{(R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B})/R_{S,B}^2}{(R_{S,V}+R_{sky,V})/R_{S,V}^2}}
=\frac{\sqrt{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}/R_{S,B}}{\sqrt{R_{S,V}+R_{sky,V}}/R_{S,V}}.$$  
Thus  
$$t_B=\frac{T_{tot}\,\sqrt{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}/R_{S,B}}
{\sqrt{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}/R_{S,B}+\sqrt{R_{S,V}+R_{sky,V}}/R_{S,V}},$$  
$$t_V=T_{tot}-t_B.$$  
4. Substituting back gives the minimum error  
$$\sigma_{B-V,\min}
=\frac{2.5}{\ln10}\,\frac{\displaystyle\frac{\sqrt{R_{S,B}+R_{sky,B}}}{R_{S,B}}
+\displaystyle\frac{\sqrt{R_{S,V}+R_{sky,V}}}{R_{S,V}}}
{\sqrt{T_{tot}}}.$$
